TO MAKE DOUGH: Cream sugar and butter in mixer; add egg. Beat in flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Form into two balls. Cover and chill 20 to 30 minutes. Roll one portion of the dough to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface. Cut with cookie cutters and place on ungreased cookie sheets. Repeat with remaining dough. Bake in a preheated 350 degrees F oven 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 1 to 2 minutes on baking sheet and then transfer to cooling rack. Ice and decorate as desired. TO MAKE ICING: Combine powdered sugar, corn syrup, almond extract and enough milk for desired spreading consistency. Tint with food coloring, if desired.